Name: Cedar Mountain
Directions_1: Travel North on Highway 13, then East (right) to Rifle Gap State Park.
Directions_2: At the East park entrance, enter the park and follow the park road west approx. 1.5 miles to the Sage Campground.
Directions_3: From the north end of the campground, travel north on the dirt road approximately 1/2 mile.

Name: West Elk Ridge
Directions_1: Travel north on 7th Street to Buford Road until intersection with Grass Valley Road, stay north on Buford Road
Directions_2: Turn west onto CR 247 (N Cutoff Road) for 1.25 miles.
Directions_3: BLM Road 8114 is to the north (right)

Name: Teakee Mine
Directions_1: Travel North on 7th street to Buford Road for 3.5 miles.
Directions_2: Turn north on CR 243 (Main Elk Creek) for 1/2 mile.
Directions_3: Turn north on BLM route 8132 heading west.

Name: Gibson Gulch
Directions_1: Travel south acress the Colorado River to CR 335 (Colorado River Rd.)
Directions_2: Travel east approximately 7 miles to CR 311 (Divide Creek Rd).Travel for another 7 miles south.
Directions_3: Turn east on BLM road 8214 (Gibson Gulch)
Directions_4: Private land lies directly north of road 8214 for 1.5 miles. Avoid gas well pads. Pinon trees can be found 2 miles up BLM road 8214.

Name: Red Hill
Directions_1: Travel 1.5 miles south on Valley Road. Turn west onto CR 10A (Cottonwood Pass Road).
Directions_2: Proceed for 3 miles to the first cattleguard and turn northwest onto CR 76. Pinon trees are found after 1/2 mile.

Name: Dry Lake 8460
Directions_1: From I-70, travel north on County road 51 (Trail Gulch Road) for 4 miles to BLM information kiosk.
Directions_2: Proceed west on BLM 8460. Pinion trees are to the south of the road.
Directions_3: No tree cutting in nearby private land parcels.

Name: Dry Lake Sawmill/ Agnew
Directions_1: From I-70, travel north on County road 51 (Trail Gulch Road) for 4 miles to BLM information kiosk.
Directions_2: Cutting area is between Agnew Gulch and the old sawmill (CR 50).
Directions_3: No tree cutting in nearby private land parcels

Name: Dry Rifle- Walk In
Directions_1: Travel north on Highway 13, then east on Highway 325.
Directions_2: After Rifle Gap Reservoir, turn east onto Grass Valley Road (CR 226).
Directions_3: Travel approximately 1 mile to BLM parking area on the right.

Name: Spring Creek
Directions_1: Exit at Gypsum (exit 140) and drive south on Highway 6 to Valley Road.
Directions_2: Turn left on the Cooley Mesa Road (CR 102), and drive south 1 mile to BLM road 8380 (North Hardscrabble Road).
Directions_3: Turn left onto BLM 8380.
Directions_4: Travel 3/4 mile on 8380 to 8380DA. Turn left onto 8380DA, proceed 1/2 mile into wood cutting area.

Name: Cedar Mountain Area 1
Directions_1: Exit at Rifle (exit 90) and travel north on Highway 13 through Rifle.
Directions_2: Proceed around the lake and turn left into the state park. Show the attendant your wood permit.
Directions_3: At the Sage Campground, drive north on access road 8090.
Directions_4: Cross over a cattleguard and travel 1/2 mile to the wood cutting boundary.

Name: Cedar Mountain Area 2
Directions_1: Exit at Rifle (exit 90) and travel north on Highway 13 through Rifle.
Directions_2: Proceed around the lake and turn left into the state park. Show the attendant your wood permit.
Directions_3: At the Sage Campground, drive north on access road 8090.
Directions_4: Cross over a cattleguard and travel 2 miles to the wood cutting area.

Name: Spring Creek Burn
Directions_1: Exit at Gypsum (exit 140) and drive south on Highway 6 to Valley Road.
Directions_2: Turn left on Cooley Mesa Road (CR 102), and drive south 1 mile to BLM road 8380 (North Hardscrabble Road).
Directions_3: Turn left onto BLM 8380.
Directions_4: Travel 1 1/2 miles on 8380 to wood cutting area.

Name: Gypsum Hills
Directions_1: Exit at Gypsum (exit 140) and proceed north on Trail Gulch Road (County Road 51) past the Gypsum Mine (approx. 4 miles)
Directions_2: Turn left onto BLM road 8460 for approximately 1/2 mile to woodcutting area on the south side of the road.

Name: Gypsum Hills
Directions_1: Exit at Gypsum (exit 140) and proceed north on Trail Gulch Road (County Road 51) past the Gypsum Mine (approx. 4 miles)
Directions_2: Turn left onto BLM road 8460 for approximately 1/2 mile to woodcutting area on the south side of the road.

Name: Beehive
Directions_1: go east on I-70
Directions_2: Continue on 333 for 1.7 miles and turn right onto Nichols Gravel Pit Road for 0.6 miles.
Directions_3: Turn left on KE Road for 0.9 miles, then right onto 51.1 Road.
Directions_4: Continue for 3.4 miles until you reach the cutting area.

Name: Bull Hill
Directions_1: go south on U.S. Highway 50 to Whitewater
Directions_2: Turn Right onto Road 10.80 for 2.3 miles to the first cutting area on the left.
Directions_3: Go up to 1.1 miles to the other 2 cutting areas on the left.

Name: Maverick
Directions_1: go south on U.S. Highway 50 to Whitewater
Directions_2: Continue straight past the turn for road 10.80. 630 turns into FS405. Travel for 2.8 miles and turn right on route 11.30.
Directions_3: Travel for 0.4 miles on 11.30 to the cutting area.

Name: Outlaw Mesa
Directions_1: go south on Hwy 50 to Whitewater. Turn right on CO Hwy 141 and drive approximately 40 miles
Directions_2: Z2.30 is a 3.5 mile loop that will retun you to 19.50.
Directions_3: There are two more areas past the 2nd junction of Z2.30 and 19.50 at 0.3 miles on the right, and 0.7 miles on the left.

Name: Toms Canyon
Directions_1: go west on Colorado 340 to Monument Road. Turn left on to Monument Road and travel ~8 miles to DS.00 Road (Glade Park Turnoff).
Directions_2: Continue past the store for approximately 12.9 miles. The first cutting area entrance is on the right (BLM 7130B)
Directions_3: 0.8 miles down BLM 7130B is another entrance to the cutting area.

Name: Mud Springs
Directions_1: go west on Colorado 340 to Monument Road. Turn left on to Monument Road and travel ~8 miles to DS.00 Road (Glade Park Turnoff).
Directions_2: Turn left onto 16.50 Road and continue for approximately 6.8 miles.
Directions_3: Cutting areas are on both sides of 16.50 road. Ensure you remain on public land.

Name: Glade Park Store
Directions_1: go west on Colorado 340 to Monument Road. Turn left on to Monument Road and travel ~8 miles to DS.00 Road (Glade Park Turnoff).
Directions_2: Turn left onto 16.50 Road and continue for approximately 2.8 miles to Miller Canyon Ranch Road
Directions_3: Turn left on Miller Canyon Ranch Road. Travel approximately 1/2 mile to cutting area on both sides of the road.

Name: Monument
Directions_1: go west on Colorado 340 to Monument Road. Turn left on to Monument Road and travel ~8 miles to DS.00 Road (Glade Park Turnoff).
Directions_2: From Intersection of BLM Q160, continue approximately 0.6 miles on DS.00 Road to BLM Q170. Second cutting area is west of the BLM road and north of DS.00 Road.
Directions_3: From the Intersection of BLM Q170 (second area), travel approximately 0.8 miles to cutting area 3 North of DS.00 Road.
Directions_4: From cutting area 3, travel approximately 1/4 mile to BLM Q170. Turn right and travel .4 miles to the cutting area on both sides of the road.

Name: Pine Gulch
Directions_1: go east on I70. Take the DeBeque exit and head north over the river. Turn left onto E. 4th Street.
Directions_2: Travel on V 2/10 Rd for 18 miles. The first cutting area is on the left side of the road. The second area is 2.8 miles further.

Name: Jackson
Directions_1: go east on I70. Take the DeBeque exit and head north over the river. Turn left onto E. 4th Street.
Directions_2: Travel on V 2/10 Rd for approximately 10.7 miles to 36 2/10 Rd. Turn left into the middle of the cutting area south of V 2/10 Road.

Name: Lane Gulch
Directions_1: go east on I70. Take the DeBeque exit and head north over the river. Turn left onto E. 4th Street.
Directions_2: Travel on V 2/10 Rd for 18 miles. Turn left to remain on V 2/10 Rd. Travel for approximately 2.8 miles to the cutting area.

Name: North Fork Kannah Creek
Directions_1: travel south on US 50 for 13.5 miles. Turn left on Kannah Creek Road.

Name: Brandon Ditch
Directions_1: travel south on US 50 for 13.5 miles. Turn left on Kannah Creek Road.
Directions_2: Travel approximately 1.8 miles to the cutting area on the left.

Name: Ashmeed
Directions_1: go east on I70. Take the DeBeque exit and go south.
Directions_2: Turn right onto BLM 7803. The first cutting area is 1/2 mile up the road for 3/4 miles.
Directions_3: The second cutting area is 1/2 mile past the first for 1/2 mile.

Name: Farmers Canyon

Name: Monument

Name: John Brown
Directions_1: go south on Hwy 50 to Whitewater. Turn right on CO Hwy 141 and drive approx. 45 miles to Gateway. Go past Gateway on 141 and turn right on John Brown Canyon Road and continue to the cutting area which will be marked with a BLM sign.

Name: Tom's Canyon
Directions_1: go west on Colorado 340 to Monument Road.Turn left onto Monument Road,and travel 8 miles, through Colorado National Monument, to DS Road (Glade Park Turnoff) and take a left. Stay on the DS Road and go past Glade Park Store approximately 13.5 miles until you see 5.7 Road. Tom's Canyon turnoff is 1/4 mile past 5.7 Road on the right and will be signed.
